#
IMMAPP1
Character to consider for immship:
Position / responsibility sought:

1.  What is the highest level (mortal levels and immortal levels included)
    that you have attained on Crimson Mud 2?  How recently did you
    attain / held the rank?

2.  How long have you mudded on Crimson Mud 2?

3.  Have you played other muds?  If so, what levels have you attained
   (mortal and immortal, please).

4.  Do you have any experience in mud administration?  Please keep in mind,
    this does not necessarily refer to running a mud or being in charge of 
    one.  Carrying out administrative duties (communications, coding, etc.)
    is also included.

5.  Do you have any coding experience (C, C+, Unix, etc.)?  If so, do you 
    have any examples of your work?

6.  Do you have any experience zoning?  This includes creating zones, 
    balancing zones, or any aspect of zone creation or modification.  If so,
    are there any examples of your work?

7.  Do you have any experience creating / designing webpages?  If so, are 
    there any examples of your work?

8.  As an immortal, you may be faced with many challenges and concerns.
    How are you at public relations?  Can you cope with anger, insults,
    questions?  Can you contribute solutions or ideas to help solve 
    problems?  Are you friendly?  Can you interact with others?

9.  How good would you say you are at brainstorming ideas?   Can you help
    others come up with ideas?

10. Do you enjoy quests?  Would you enjoy holding quests?  Do you have 
    ideas for future quests?  (Please include quests that you have enjoyed
    [styles, no direct examples are required] and the reasons you enjoyed 
    them.)

SEE ALSO: IMMAPP2

#
IMMAPP2
11.  Please select the following preferences:

     Which do you prefer: Teaching or Creating?
     Which do you prefer: Playing or Observing?
     Which do you prefer: Quest making or Mud building?
     Which do you prefer: Designing or Implementing?

12.  In a short paragraph, please tell us your work habits.  Please include
     your relations to other workers (do you enjoy teamwork?), your 
     dedication to your work (do you take it seriously, or is it for money?)
     , & how you handle problems (if something happens that sets back your 
     work, how do you fix it?).

13.  In a short paragraph, please tell us about yourself.  Looks / religious
     beliefs / nationality / skin color are not what we seek.  Describe your
     attitudes, your likes and dislikes, and anything else that lets us see
     what you are like.

14.  In a short paragraph, tell us what it means to you to be an immortal.
     Why do you want to be an immortal?  What motivates you to apply to 
     become one of the administrative members of Crimson Mud 2?

15.  Finally, what do you do outside of Crimson 2?  Are you a student?  Do 
     you have a full or part-time   job?  What activities might limit or 
     contribute to your abilities as an immortal for Crimson Mud 2?

#
NORENT NO_RENT

No_rent equipment means that when you leave the game with that particular
item, it will dissapear.

#
BOWS CROSSBOWS ARROWS BOLTS SHOOT

Usage: grab <bow/crossbow>
- You must grab the bow before you can load it with an arrow or bolt.

Usage: load <arrow/bolt>
- This will put your ammunition into the bow or crossbow.

Usage: shoot <target>
- You can shoot mobs, players, even yourself (suicidal tendancies??)


Damage levels
-------------
Arrow / Poisoned Arrow :  300 dmg
Bolt  / Poisoned Bolt  :  600 dmg
Deadly Bolt            : 1500 dmg


You can purchase all of these items at the Questmaster in Midgaard.

#
DOFOR

Usage: dofor <avat/mort/gods/quest/level/all/count> <command(s)>

Dofor is a command so you can do something for multiple people or
multiple things at once.  This is a IMMORTAL command.

In all dofor command the # symbol is used for your list of targets
all but count use this for player names, count uses it for its numbers.

dofor avat  = for all avats
dofor mort  = for all morts
dofor gods  = for all gods (lower level than user)
dofor quest = for all people with <QUEST> flag on
dofor all   = for everyone online under user level
dofor level = for you to define the level range, examples:
              dofor level 20 30 = for levels 20 to 30 only
              dofor level 10 40 = for levels 10 to 40 only
dofor count = IMP only, can set a defined amount times dofor is used
              or that is use for a list of numbers, examples:
              dofor count 30 say hi, would say hi 31 times. (counts 0)
              dofor count 10 say #, would say 0-10

Some more examples:

dofor all gossip Hi #! = this would gossip hi to all under user level
dofor level 1 5 cast sanc # = this would sanc everyone levels 1-5
dofor quest restore # = this would restore everyone with <QUEST> flag
dofor count 24 load obj xxx = would load the object 25 times (counts 0)

#
OTRANSFER

Usage: otransfer <obj>
       or
       otransfer <obj> <target>

Use this to brings objects to yourself that are already in existance in
the game.  Can target equipment in objects, on the ground, on players or
mobs.  You can also send objects to other players.


#
INCOGNITO

Players at a lower level will not see you on the who list, and only
hear [Someone] on the global channels.  In the same room they'll be
able to see you, and hear your says.  Players at a higher lvl than the
set lvl will see an <INCOGNITO level> flag after your name in the who
list.

#
GHOST

This can also be set at a level like invis.  You will be seen on the
who list, and the global channels will show your name. but you will
not be seen in the same room by players lower than the set level.
Says will be from [Someone].  Imms at your level or higher will see
a <GHOST level> flag after your name in the who list.

#
BLESS_COMMAND

Bless utilizes a total of 25 spells.  These are:  aid [106], bless [3],
armor [1],improved invisibility [9], detect evil [18], detect good [85],
detect invisibility [19],detect magic [20], protection from evil [34],
sanctuary major [36], strength [39],sense life [44], darksight [68],
regeneration [74], breathwater [87], waterwalk [93],bind souls [151],
demon flesh [142], demonic aid [127], intelligence [131], wisdom [132],
dexterity [133], constitution [134], charisma [135] and fly [154].


To use bless, simply type bless <target>.

NOTE: The spells will only work if you have them practiced.


#
MAIL MUDMAIL MUD_MAIL MESSAGES

To use mud-based mail, use the mail commands.  Type mail for a list of 
options available to you. The current list of commands are as follows (keep
in mind each command should be preceeded by the word mail):

read    <msg>
write   <name> <topic>
remove  <msg>
list
clear

See also: BOARDS

#
LOGVIEW

Usage: viewlog <file alias> [number of lines to display]

    This command is used for viewing log files online. There are several
valid syntaxes that can be used. If you type "logview" with no parameters,
it will display a list with file aliases on the left, and the path name they
refer to on the right. You will use these file aliases to tell this command
which log file you want to view. For the rest of the optional parameters,
please see the following examples.

    Example 1: logview mainlog
    (Displays the last 15 lines in the "main" log)

    Example 2: logview mainlog 10
    (Displays the last 10 lines in the "main" log)


Credits for this command go to: Tyler Barnes<tyler.barnes@crcn.net>
See also: LOGSEARCH

#
LOGSEARCH

Usage: logsearch <file alias> [lines to show] <text to search for>

    This command is used to search log files for specified text. If you type
logsearch with no parameters, it will give you a list of file aliases on the
left (the name you will refer to the file as), and the path that each alias
refers to on the right. Logsearch accepts three parameters. The file alias
which I just explained, lines to show, and text to search for. Lines to
show is the maximum number of lines that you want to be displayed that match
your criteria. This is an optional parameter. If you do not specify the
max number of lines to show, logsearch will default to a max of 15. The text
to search for should be self explanatory.

As an example, if an immortal was stat'ing equipment/mobs illegally and you
wanted to find out who it was, you might type the following:

logsearch godcmds 50 stat

That would search the "godcmds" log and return the first 50 lines found that
contain the text "stat". This command is NOT case sensitive.

Credits for this command go to: Tyler Barnes<tyler.barnes@crcn.net>
SEE ALSO: LOGVIEW

#
MULTIPLAYING MULTIS ALTS MULTI-PLAY

Multiplaying is defined as using more than one player character online at 
a time.  This is not illegal for levels 1-41 and there is no set limit to
how many chars you can have online at a time (within reason).

We hope you will multiplay responsibly if you do so at all. This rule is
subject to change if abused.

Immortals MAY NOT multi-play.

Thank you,

C2 Admins

#
NEDRA

Nedra is a boon to all mortals.  Located up from Market Square, Nedra is
known to cast a few helpful spells when you take a moment to relax in her
room.

#
RAHNKARA

Rahnkara is the head priestess in the Temple of T'Salchoic.  You can buy
statistics, heals and cures from her.  She is intolerant of violence around
her, though.  You will not be able to fight when she is in the same room as
you are.

#
"NEW RULES"

You can not bid from Jail.  This is a bug and doing so will result in
anywhere from a longer jail time, (while frozen) or loss of items.

If something seems illegal, or seems like it could be against the rules
then theres a chance it is and by following through and doing it could
and can result in some form of punishment.  This falls under ALL rule and
non-rule catagories respect it.

If someone tells you something is a rule and you cannot find it in the
helpfiles, news, or posts, follow it as such until you can confirm it from
an administrator.  If you are still unsure you may ask a boss.

#
AGE

Age reflects the number of mud years that you have played on C2.
Age can be affected by amount of game play, plus equipment can alter age.
The higher the age you possess, the stronger your spells become.
Mana regeneration also increases with age.

#
KILL

A kill is any successful fight where a player ends the existence of
another player or a mob. The final awarding of gold/experience from
the kill indicates the successful kill.  If auto aggression is not
set, you may not necessarily kill a mob.  You may only incapacitate
on it.
Also a good way to start a fight.

SEE ALSO: HIT

#
GECHO

An immortal command.  Allows for messaging without giving
the name of the immortal using the command which is seen throughout
the MUD world.

SEE ALSO: ECHO

#
OEDIT

An immortal command, which is yet incomplete.

#
IGNORE

A command available for all players.  You can "block" irritable or
unwanted conversation from individual players by using the ignore
command.  For example, "ignore plato" would ignore player named Plato.

#
SPIRIT

This is to replace the Legend level.  It is a quasi state of exisitance.
You are not quite mortal, but not quite a god either.
This is a purely social level and NOT a part of the imm staff, so
please let these lost souls rest in peace.

#
NWIZLIST

Syntax: nwizlist (lists imms level 43-75)

        nwizlist [avat/spirit/god/all] (lists their respective titles)

Fairly accurate way of checking what imms, avatars, and spirits exist.

#
QUEST_GOLD

Most quests generally call for a generous amount of gold.  It is useless to
restrict exact amounts for individual quests.  However, these are the
suggestions I'd make:

For level 10 or lower, do not give out more than 1 mil gold per individual
in the quest.  Morts of this area do not require much gold at all.  Giving
out 1 mil gold should be rare in itself.

From level 10 to level 20, do not give out more than 3 mil gold per
individual in the quest.  Again, morts in these levels do not need much.
White potions and recalls are the major expenses for them.

From level 20 to level 30, do not give out more than 5 mil gold per
individual in the quest.  At this point, things are starting to get more
expensive, but they do not have any insanely bad mobs or rent issues, so
they don't need a solid gold base.

From level 30 to level 40, do not give out more than 10 mil gold per
individual in the quest.  These people are working on becoming avatars,
so they may be investing in avat gear, buying stats, etc.  These are the
levels where gold is appreciated the most as a prize.

Level 41, Avatar - Quests for avats are diverse, from the incredibly easy to
the perversely hard.  I would argue that there are occasions where 1 mil 
gold is understandable and where 100 mil gold is understandable.  I would 
say no more than 200 mil gold per individual on a quest.  If there is a 
quest that requires more than that per individual, the players were insane 
to accept that quest.

See also: QUEST_QPS

#
QUEST_QPS

QPS is already much simpler to handle than gold.  Each quest point is worth
10K gold IF SOLD TO QUESTMASTER.  However, to buy a quest point, it is 20K
gold. So using quest points in quests can be money savers OR money makers
for players.

Basically, follow equivalents for gold and qps.

Ex: level 1 to 10 with 1 mil gold max would thus be 100 qps.

See also: QUEST_GOLD

#
QUEST_EMAX

Here is the CURRENT list of what is considered max for each level base.
(this could change at any time, so always check up before loading things)
Max eq is NOT to be loaded in any quest.

Under no circumstance should any of this information of what is max be
given out or told to other players.  If you already knew it was max, as
your mortal you can say as such, but as your imm you cannot.  If you didn't
know, then it is immortal only information and should stay as such.

Lists are in the following individual helpfiles as it was too spacy for
one: QUEST_EMAX_41_EVIL,QUEST_EMAX_41_GOOD, QUEST_EMAX_30, QUEST_EMAX_20, 
QUEST_EMAX_10, QUEST_EMAX_NEWBIE

Second, NO_RENT eq is encouraged over regular eq, cause in most cases it is
better, or much better than anything that can be found, which compensates
for the lack of it being permanent.  Some NO_RENT eq is EXTREMELY good and
should have approval for use.  A list will be compiled of NON_APPROVAL
NO_RENT eq and will be located in the helpfile QUEST_NO_RENT.

Third, equipment that has fewer than 5 copies in the game cannot be used.
We do not want to compete with natural pop ratios.  Eq used in quests are
to SUBSIDIZE, not outshine, natural eq popping.

Fourth, do not use any eq with less than 3% pop rate.  Even if it isn't max
or second max.  This eq is meant to be intentionally rare.  3% or higher
pop ratio, please.

There are occasions when quest rules may be modified to fit situation, when 
pop % or # in game can be disregarded.  You must see an Administrator to go
beyond those rules.  
 
See also: QUEST_GOLD QUEST_QPS
#
